sql:
SELECT AVG(income_level) 
FROM respondents 
WHERE respondent_age > 30 AND has_bank_account = 'Yes';

external_knowledge:
- 'Harbingers of data' refers to the 'users with the role "Data Collector"'.;
- 'Sailing under the banner of the "Data Collector"' means they are classified under the role "Data Collector".;
- 'Brought their treasures' signifies the act of making data collections.;
- 'The land of ID 1' corresponds to the country identified by the ID 1.;
- 'The titles of their reports' refers to the titles of the reports created by these users.

- "sailing on the financial river" is a metaphorical expression for having a bank account;
- "inhabitants" refers to respondents in the survey;
- "more than half of their inhabitants sailing on the financial river" means more than half of the respondents have a bank account.
